<h2><span id="1._c3_-_Saragossa_Opening">1. c3 - Saragossa Opening</span></h2>
<p>A rarely played move as it takes away the Knight's developing square c3. It is likely to transpose into a London System, Torre attack, Colle system, or Macleod Attack where the pawn structure is generally c3, d4, e3, or e5 depending on black's moves.
</p>
<h2><span id="Statistics">Statistics</span></h2>
<p>No statistics as 1. c3 occurs rarely among serious chess players.
</p>
